					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3290299#post-3570628</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3290299/the-little-robot-that-could#post-3570628</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 14 Aug 2017 21:43:19 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Shaggydredlocks</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1722371</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Cute as hell, and that final line sold me on an upvote.</p> <p>It's narration comes across as a little more childish than its speech in the mainlist article, so it's voice feels a bit inconsistent between the two works, but it's not wildly different.</p> <p>I would have preferred some interaction with the outside world/the 001, because it would have been interesting to see how 2785, whose purpose is to serve humans, tries to fulfill the needs of what's become of humanity; and also because this could have been any XK and worked just as well.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
